# KinStay Massanutten — Mountain House Website

## What This Does
A one-page marketing site for **KinStay Massanutten**, a 4-bedroom short-term-rental house at
Massanutten Resort in McGaheysville, VA. It showcases the property with a photo gallery,
amenities, area guide, and FAQ, and funnels visitors to the Airbnb and VRBO listings to book.
It's a static site hosted on GitHub Pages at **https://kinstay.com**.

## Setup
No build step — it's plain HTML/CSS/JS.

**Preview locally** (from this folder):
```bash
python -m http.server 8000
# then open http://localhost:8000
```
Or just double-click `index.html`.

**Deploy:** copy the entire contents of this folder into your GitHub Pages repo and push.
The `CNAME` file keeps the custom domain (kinstay.com) pointed at the site.

## Usage
Edit `index.html` for content, `css/styles.css` for styling, and `js/main.js` for the
gallery list and interactions. To add or swap photos, drop optimized images into
`images/gallery/` (a `<slug>.jpg` full-size + `<slug>-thumb.jpg` thumbnail) and add an entry
to the `PHOTOS` array in `js/main.js`.

## Environment Variables
None — fully static, no secrets. The only config is the **direct-booking form**: it posts to
[Web3Forms](https://web3forms.com), so paste your free access key into the `access_key` hidden
field in `index.html` (search for `YOUR-WEB3FORMS-ACCESS-KEY`). Inquiries are emailed to the
address you used to create the key. Spam protection uses hCaptcha with Web3Forms' shared sitekey
(no setup); swap the `data-sitekey` if you register your own hCaptcha or Cloudflare Turnstile.

## Live Availability Calendar
The calendar in the "Book direct" section greys out nights that are booked on Airbnb/VRBO.

> ⚠️ **Do not put your raw Airbnb/VRBO iCal URLs in `js/availability.js` or anywhere in this
> repo.** Those feeds contain guest data (reservation confirmation codes and the last 4 digits
> of guests' phone numbers), and this repo is public. The URLs must live **server-side only**,
> in the Cloudflare Worker below. Two reasons we need the Worker at all: (1) browsers can't fetch
> the Airbnb/VRBO `.ics` directly (no CORS headers), and (2) it keeps the feed URLs + guest data
> off the public site.

**Setup (~10 min, free):**

1. **Get your iCal export URLs** (you'll paste them into the Worker, not the repo):
   - Airbnb: Calendar → Availability → *Connect to another website* → **Export calendar** → copy the link.
   - VRBO: Calendar → the `...` menu → **Export/Import** → **Export calendar** → copy the link.

2. **Deploy this Cloudflare Worker** (dash.cloudflare.com → Workers & Pages → Create → paste,
   then edit the two URLs). It fetches both feeds server-side, keeps **only** the booked dates
   (DTSTART/DTEND — strips confirmation codes, phone digits, names), merges them, and adds CORS:
   ```js
   const FEEDS = [
     "https://www.airbnb.com/calendar/ical/40027295.ics?t=a1724a25459b4eb48cf5253552082cff",
     "PASTE_YOUR_VRBO_ICAL_URL_HERE"
   ];
   export default {
     async fetch() {
       try {
         const texts = await Promise.all(FEEDS.map(u => fetch(u).then(r => r.text())));
         let out = "BEGIN:VCALENDAR\nVERSION:2.0\n";
         const evRe = /BEGIN:VEVENT[\s\S]*?END:VEVENT/g;
         for (let t of texts) {
           t = t.replace(/\r\n[ \t]/g, "").replace(/\n[ \t]/g, ""); // unfold
           for (const ev of t.match(evRe) || []) {
             const s = (ev.match(/DTSTART[^:]*:([0-9T]+)/) || [])[1];
             const e = (ev.match(/DTEND[^:]*:([0-9T]+)/) || [])[1];
             if (s) out += "BEGIN:VEVENT\nDTSTART:" + s + (e ? "\nDTEND:" + e : "") + "\nEND:VEVENT\n";
           }
         }
         out += "END:VCALENDAR\n";
         return new Response(out, {
           headers: {
             "Content-Type": "text/calendar; charset=utf-8",
             "Access-Control-Allow-Origin": "https://kinstay.com",
             "Cache-Control": "public, max-age=1800"
           }
         });
       } catch {
         return new Response("error", { status: 502, headers: { "Access-Control-Allow-Origin": "*" } });
       }
     }
   };
   ```

3. **Point the site at it:** set `endpoint` in `js/availability.js` to your Worker URL
   (e.g. `"https://kinstay-cal.<you>.workers.dev"`).

The calendar shows availability only; it does not take bookings. Until `endpoint` is set it
renders normally and points guests to the Airbnb/VRBO links.

## Project Structure
```
Website/
├── index.html          # the page (content + SEO/meta + structured data)
├── css/styles.css       # all styling; brand palette defined in :root
├── js/main.js           # header, mobile nav, gallery + lightbox (PHOTOS array lives here)
├── images/
│   ├── hero.jpg          # hero background
│   ├── og-image.jpg      # social-share preview (1200x630)
│   ├── logo.png / logo-cream.png
│   ├── favicon-*.png, apple-touch-icon.png, icon-512.png
│   └── gallery/          # <slug>.jpg (full) + <slug>-thumb.jpg (grid)
├── CNAME                # custom domain for GitHub Pages
├── robots.txt, sitemap.xml
├── README.md, TASKS.md
└── .gitignore
```

